### Is this a regression?
no


### Description
According to https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/defineProperty, the operator 'delete' should not delete a property defined by Object.defineProperty with configurable: false. However, it is not the case in angular. 

It works ok in a normal html. I also tried to remove the polyfills, but had no luck. I don't understand why it happens as it seems to be a browser issue, but my tests show that  it only happens to angular framework. So my guess is angular rewrites the Object.defineProperty method somewhere, plz correct me if i am wrong.

## 🔬 Minimal Reproduction
https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-issue-repro2-tajv9d

try this code on the default browser console and the angular project console in stackblitz:
<code><pre>var obj = {};
Object.defineProperty(obj, 'p1', {
      configurable: false,
      enumerable: true,
      value: 'p1'
});
delete obj.p1;
</pre></code>
