### Versions
```
"@ngtools/webpack": "^7.1.2"
```

### Repro steps

Declare this class:
```
export class Test {
    static TESTVAR: string = /* @bar */ "mystring" /* @/bar */;
}
```
and run it through `@ngtools/webpack`. It outputs this:

```
var Test = /** @class */ (function () {
    function Test() {
    }
    Test.TESTVAR = "mystring" /* @/bar */;
}());
```


### Desired functionality

It should not eat the comment, so it'd still be processable by other loaders. Like this:
```
var Test = /** @class */ (function () {
    function Test() {
    }
    Test.TESTVAR = /* @bar */ "mystring" /* @/bar */;
}
```

